1
00:00:08,600 --> 00:00:10,961
♪Love's little quiz
takes seven parts sweet♪

2
00:00:10,962 --> 00:00:13,559
♪And three parts bitter,
till you and I meet♪

3
00:00:13,560 --> 00:00:17,159
♪I pretend I'm not there,
but secretly stay♪

4
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:26,399
♪Waiting for you♪

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:31,400
♪We've got so many
romantic dreams to unfold♪

6
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:36,224
♪Finally hearing
the I love you I long to hold♪

7
00:00:36,225 --> 00:00:39,839
♪Falling fast
into the swirl of your eyes♪

8
00:00:39,840 --> 00:00:42,399
♪It's just too tempting, so tempting♪

9
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:45,499
♪Never could I have guessed♪

10
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:46,499
♪My heart's rhythm♪

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:49,632
♪How beautiful it is, meeting you♪

12
00:01:02,975 --> 00:01:05,961
=Late to Love=
(Adapted from "My Husband Is A Billionaire!")

13
00:01:05,962 --> 00:01:09,107
=Episode 3=

14
00:01:09,339 --> 00:01:11,299
I want you to show some real sincerity

15
00:01:11,300 --> 00:01:12,900
and beg me nicely,

16
00:01:13,660 --> 00:01:15,459
instead of using that arrogant CEO tone

17
00:01:15,460 --> 00:01:16,819
to micromanage my life.

18
00:01:16,820 --> 00:01:18,138
You think you look cool?

19
00:01:18,139 --> 00:01:20,379
You want me to beg you? I...

20
00:01:25,940 --> 00:01:26,939
Hello?

21
00:01:28,139 --> 00:01:29,900
You want me to move my car?

22
00:01:30,339 --> 00:01:31,939
Got it. I'm on my way.

23
00:01:31,940 --> 00:01:33,058
I'll be right there.

24
00:01:33,059 --> 00:01:34,980
Isn't the car right here?

25
00:01:35,779 --> 00:01:36,899
Xu Nange,

26
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:40,459
could you please move into my place?

27
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:42,618
Do me a favor, please?

28
00:01:42,619 --> 00:01:43,899
What did you say? I didn't catch that.

29
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:44,819
Xu Nange, I...

30
00:01:44,820 --> 00:01:45,980
Alright, let's move.

31
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:49,379
Get in. Hurry up.

32
00:01:49,820 --> 00:01:50,700
Shen Yan.

33
00:01:52,699 --> 00:01:53,860
Let's go.

34
00:01:55,139 --> 00:01:55,739
Dad,

35
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:57,099
let me introduce you.

36
00:01:57,100 --> 00:01:58,700
This is Xu Nange.

37
00:01:58,859 --> 00:02:00,019
This is my father,

38
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:01,299
and this is my grandma.

39
00:02:01,460 --> 00:02:02,780
Nice to meet you, Mr. Huo.

40
00:02:03,339 --> 00:02:04,539
Nice to meet you, Grandma.

41
00:02:08,099 --> 00:02:09,220
Nange,

42
00:02:09,260 --> 00:02:10,500
nice to meet you.

43
00:02:12,779 --> 00:02:13,739
Nange,

44
00:02:13,740 --> 00:02:14,699
don't mind her.

45
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:16,899
She's our family matriarch.
She's in her 70s now.

46
00:02:16,900 --> 00:02:20,259
She has dementia, so she doesn't
remember people or past events anymore.

47
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:22,098
Mom,

48
00:02:22,099 --> 00:02:23,938
this is your granddaughter-in-law,

49
00:02:23,939 --> 00:02:25,659
Xu Nange.

50
00:02:31,659 --> 00:02:33,539
What's wrong, Nange?

51
00:02:33,580 --> 00:02:34,979
Low blood sugar?

52
00:02:41,819 --> 00:02:43,498
I'll be fine as long as I get

53
00:02:43,499 --> 00:02:44,938
an early night tonight.

54
00:02:44,939 --> 00:02:46,419
Don't worry about it, Mr. Huo.

55
00:02:46,420 --> 00:02:47,058
Come on.

56
00:02:47,059 --> 00:02:48,459
You two are already married.

57
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:50,259
Why are you still calling me Mr. Huo?

58
00:02:54,260 --> 00:02:56,659
Well, we haven't had the wedding yet.

59
00:02:57,300 --> 00:02:59,139
She should go through the tea ceremony

60
00:02:59,140 --> 00:03:00,620
before changing how she addresses you.

61
00:03:00,819 --> 00:03:01,979
Yeah.

62
00:03:02,539 --> 00:03:04,818
You really know
your traditional etiquette. Very well.

63
00:03:04,819 --> 00:03:06,658
My mom is definitely going to love you.

64
00:03:06,659 --> 00:03:08,060
Right, Mom?

65
00:03:13,779 --> 00:03:14,699
Nange,

66
00:03:14,740 --> 00:03:16,979
you seem really ill.

67
00:03:20,059 --> 00:03:21,060
Yeah.

68
00:03:21,539 --> 00:03:24,340
I am actually feeling a bit
under the weather today.

69
00:03:27,379 --> 00:03:28,938
In that case,
let's catch up another day.

70
00:03:28,939 --> 00:03:30,658
Nange isn't feeling well today.

71
00:03:30,659 --> 00:03:31,739
Alright.

72
00:03:31,740 --> 00:03:33,498
Head over to the apartment
and get some rest.

73
00:03:33,499 --> 00:03:34,218
That apartment

74
00:03:34,219 --> 00:03:36,220
will be your marital home from now on.

75
00:03:36,339 --> 00:03:36,859
It's just

76
00:03:36,860 --> 00:03:38,460
a three-minute walk from here.

77
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:41,280
That way, I won't disturb you,
but we can still look out for each other.

78
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:41,739
Go on over.

79
00:03:41,740 --> 00:03:43,419
Okay, let's head out then.

80
00:03:43,460 --> 00:03:44,460
Alright.

81
00:03:47,420 --> 00:03:48,460
Hurry up.

82
00:03:49,420 --> 00:03:50,460
Mom,

83
00:03:50,939 --> 00:03:52,338
your granddaughter-in-law

84
00:03:52,339 --> 00:03:53,699
is really great.

85
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:54,859
Wonderful.

86
00:04:04,339 --> 00:04:05,500
Read this.

87
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:08,498
What's this?

88
00:04:08,499 --> 00:04:09,699
Since you just launched

89
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:11,938
a harsh personal attack on me,

90
00:04:11,939 --> 00:04:13,139
I think

91
00:04:13,140 --> 00:04:15,379
we should
sign a supplementary agreement.

92
00:04:17,060 --> 00:04:18,418
Here's the first clause.

93
00:04:18,419 --> 00:04:20,760
Since this move
was completely unplanned,

94
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,298
(Clause 1: Disruption Compensation)
it poses a potential risk of disrupting

95
00:04:22,299 --> 00:04:23,858
the progress
of Party B's research papers.

96
00:04:23,859 --> 00:04:24,538
For instance,

97
00:04:24,539 --> 00:04:25,738
disrupting Party B's

98
00:04:25,739 --> 00:04:27,700
physical balance in any shape or form.

99
00:04:28,979 --> 00:04:31,899
Including, but not limited to,

100
00:04:31,900 --> 00:04:33,778
fabricating clinical symptoms induced

101
00:04:33,779 --> 00:04:35,338
by tripping, bumping, or shoving.

102
00:04:35,339 --> 00:04:38,059
Party A, meaning you,
will need to cover all time-related costs

103
00:04:38,060 --> 00:04:39,298
that Party B, meaning me,

104
00:04:39,299 --> 00:04:42,098
might incur as a result.

105
00:04:42,099 --> 00:04:43,059
The compensation will be

106
00:04:43,060 --> 00:04:45,459
calculated at 300% of my hourly rate.

107
00:04:45,460 --> 00:04:46,979
Hourly rate?

108
00:04:47,820 --> 00:04:49,139
Dr. Xu,

109
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:52,379
what exactly is your labor
valued at on the open market?

110
00:04:52,380 --> 00:04:54,699
As a PhD student
at Linhai Medical University,

111
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:57,218
my monthly stipend
averages about 2,800 yuan.

112
00:04:57,219 --> 00:04:59,858
Based on the legal 40-hour work week,

113
00:04:59,859 --> 00:05:01,579
that breaks down to 24.10 per hour.

114
00:05:01,580 --> 00:05:02,619
300% of that

115
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:04,218
would be 72.30 yuan.

116
00:05:04,219 --> 00:05:05,098
But given your status,

117
00:05:05,099 --> 00:05:07,298
which is incredibly high-profile,

118
00:05:07,299 --> 00:05:09,139
this could cause me
additional mental distress.

119
00:05:09,140 --> 00:05:10,259
So,

120
00:05:10,260 --> 00:05:11,499
I think we should round it up

121
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,939
to an even 100 yuan per hour.

122
00:05:12,940 --> 00:05:14,579
Keep the pocket change.
No need to thank me.

123
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:14,939
You...

124
00:05:14,940 --> 00:05:15,619
Clause two.

125
00:05:15,620 --> 00:05:17,338
My experimental data
and research materials

126
00:05:17,339 --> 00:05:19,418
require the highest level
of security clearance.

127
00:05:19,419 --> 00:05:21,338
Without my biometric authentication,

128
00:05:21,339 --> 00:05:24,459
(Clause 2: Data Security)
no one is allowed to touch anything.

129
00:05:24,460 --> 00:05:26,218
That includes you, Mr. Huo.

130
00:05:26,219 --> 00:05:27,539
No one at all?

131
00:05:28,020 --> 00:05:28,978
What if there's a fire?

132
00:05:28,979 --> 00:05:30,419
Not even firefighters?

133
00:05:31,940 --> 00:05:34,139
In case of emergency,

134
00:05:34,140 --> 00:05:35,778
I need to be
on-site to authorize access.

135
00:05:35,779 --> 00:05:37,099
Dr. Xu.

136
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:40,299
We are signing

137
00:05:40,419 --> 00:05:41,978
a cohabitation agreement here.

138
00:05:41,979 --> 00:05:43,778
It's not some nuclear launch code.

139
00:05:43,779 --> 00:05:44,658
Mr. Huo,

140
00:05:44,659 --> 00:05:46,538
my research is more important
than nuclear weapons.

141
00:05:46,539 --> 00:05:47,699
It could determine the future

142
00:05:47,700 --> 00:05:49,900
treatment path
for certain mental disorders.

143
00:05:52,020 --> 00:05:53,419
Are you done?

144
00:05:53,940 --> 00:05:55,059
My turn.

145
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:03,899
Clause one.

146
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:05,298
Party B must, in all settings

147
00:06:05,299 --> 00:06:06,459
outside the lab,

148
00:06:06,460 --> 00:06:07,579
concede that Party A holds

149
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,738
all superficial rights
of a legal spouse.

150
00:06:09,739 --> 00:06:12,259
Including, but not limited to,
holding hands, hugging,

151
00:06:12,260 --> 00:06:15,179
and intimate interaction when necessary.

152
00:06:18,419 --> 00:06:19,019
Yes.

153
00:06:19,020 --> 00:06:20,139
That's exactly the face.

154
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:20,699
Don't look

155
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:22,140
as sharp as you did just now.

156
00:06:22,620 --> 00:06:23,059
Wait,

157
00:06:23,060 --> 00:06:24,459
that's your own demand.

158
00:06:24,460 --> 00:06:25,459
You can't include that.

159
00:06:25,460 --> 00:06:26,658
Clause two.

160
00:06:26,659 --> 00:06:28,019
In front of Party A's family,

161
00:06:28,020 --> 00:06:29,778
Party B must proactively display

162
00:06:29,779 --> 00:06:31,858
a stable, loving marriage

163
00:06:31,859 --> 00:06:33,738
at least once a day.

164
00:06:33,739 --> 00:06:35,418
Within a week, you must complete

165
00:06:35,419 --> 00:06:37,059
all background reading required

166
00:06:37,060 --> 00:06:39,140
to act as the wife of Huo Group's CEO.

167
00:06:39,260 --> 00:06:40,658
That's absolutely impossible.

168
00:06:40,659 --> 00:06:41,699
Even my lab data doesn't run

169
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:42,738
that smoothly every time.

170
00:06:42,739 --> 00:06:44,059
Clause three

171
00:06:44,099 --> 00:06:46,299
is about my brother, Huo Zichen.

172
00:06:47,099 --> 00:06:47,899
No need to explain.

173
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:49,699
I get it. We need to
get our story straight.

174
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:51,379
Our marriage was totally unexpected,

175
00:06:51,380 --> 00:06:53,859
and we...

176
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:56,859
Fell hopelessly in love.

177
00:06:56,979 --> 00:06:58,260
It was love...

178
00:06:58,940 --> 00:07:00,460
at first sight.

179
00:07:02,260 --> 00:07:04,299
Can we change the wording a bit?

180
00:07:05,140 --> 00:07:06,298
We are

181
00:07:06,299 --> 00:07:09,499
the optimal match
based on a rational evaluation.

182
00:07:12,820 --> 00:07:13,979
Dr. Xu,

183
00:07:14,060 --> 00:07:15,699
Zichen isn't stupid.

184
00:07:15,700 --> 00:07:17,098
A story that's too logical

185
00:07:17,099 --> 00:07:18,380
won't fool him.

186
00:07:20,099 --> 00:07:20,979
Besides,

187
00:07:21,219 --> 00:07:23,619
you're just putting on
a little irrational performance

188
00:07:23,620 --> 00:07:25,379
in exchange for my full backing

189
00:07:25,380 --> 00:07:27,218
on your upcoming research papers,

190
00:07:27,219 --> 00:07:28,340
along with...

191
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:30,218
this entire house

192
00:07:30,219 --> 00:07:31,459
that can hold

193
00:07:31,460 --> 00:07:32,858
those nuclear weapons of yours.

194
00:07:32,859 --> 00:07:33,900
Isn't that enough?

195
00:07:35,859 --> 00:07:36,820
Deal.

196
00:07:37,539 --> 00:07:38,619
Well, I hope you

197
00:07:38,620 --> 00:07:41,260
can strictly stick
to the terms of this agreement.

198
00:07:41,460 --> 00:07:42,499
Don't worry, Mr. Huo.

199
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:43,978
Since this is a contract marriage,

200
00:07:43,979 --> 00:07:46,179
I'll definitely show
some professional integrity.

201
00:07:47,539 --> 00:07:49,499
What do you mean, contract marriage?

202
00:07:52,460 --> 00:07:53,380
Dad.

203
00:07:54,500 --> 00:07:55,940
What are you doing here?

204
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:01,019
I came over

205
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:01,899
to have Nange

206
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:03,499
pick out a car she likes,

207
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:05,979
so she has something
to drive for her daily commute.

208
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:10,218
But I just heard something
about a contract marriage.

209
00:08:10,219 --> 00:08:11,019
What's that about?

210
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:12,979
Contract marriage?

211
00:08:13,659 --> 00:08:16,059
What contract marriage?

212
00:08:16,299 --> 00:08:18,059
Contract marriage?

213
00:08:20,739 --> 00:08:22,059
Please, have a seat first.

214
00:08:29,099 --> 00:08:30,658
This is on you.

215
00:08:30,659 --> 00:08:33,139
Why did you have to use
such a cold term?

216
00:08:35,299 --> 00:08:36,899
The contract we were talking about

217
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:38,778
is just an interdisciplinary

218
00:08:38,779 --> 00:08:41,658
research project Beiyan and I built

219
00:08:41,659 --> 00:08:44,739
around our marriage.

220
00:08:46,220 --> 00:08:49,300
An interdisciplinary research project?

221
00:08:49,699 --> 00:08:50,178
Right.

222
00:08:50,179 --> 00:08:51,340
Interdisciplinary.

223
00:08:51,419 --> 00:08:52,379
Interdisciplinary.

224
00:08:52,539 --> 00:08:54,058
Interdisciplinary is great.

225
00:08:54,059 --> 00:08:55,499
That sounds pretty interesting.

226
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:57,220
Tell me more.

227
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:00,538
As you know, I'm a medical student.

228
00:09:00,539 --> 00:09:01,899
I'm used to using data

229
00:09:01,900 --> 00:09:04,778
and models to understand everything.

230
00:09:04,779 --> 00:09:06,778
Before I met Beiyan,

231
00:09:06,779 --> 00:09:08,418
marriage to me

232
00:09:08,419 --> 00:09:10,379
was just this massive,

233
00:09:10,380 --> 00:09:12,658
highly unpredictable, unknown system.

234
00:09:12,659 --> 00:09:15,538
Beiyan hoped that by treating it
like a research project,

235
00:09:15,539 --> 00:09:17,899
I could adapt to my new role
as quickly as possible

236
00:09:17,900 --> 00:09:19,178
and stop stressing out.

237
00:09:19,179 --> 00:09:20,899
So I defined this KPI

238
00:09:20,900 --> 00:09:22,899
as the initialization contract

239
00:09:22,900 --> 00:09:24,298
of our marital relationship,

240
00:09:24,299 --> 00:09:26,300
which is exactly
what you just overheard.

241
00:09:29,539 --> 00:09:31,019
Don't stress out, okay?

242
00:09:31,819 --> 00:09:33,899
I pretty much get the gist of it.

243
00:09:34,299 --> 00:09:34,778
Alright.

244
00:09:34,779 --> 00:09:36,339
I won't keep you guys, then.

245
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:37,259
You two

246
00:09:37,260 --> 00:09:38,460
can get back to your project.

247
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:39,779
Dad.

248
00:09:40,260 --> 00:09:41,139
I'll walk you out.

249
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:44,899
I didn't understand a single word.

250
00:09:50,980 --> 00:09:51,698
Alright.

251
00:09:51,699 --> 00:09:52,458
Pick one.

252
00:09:52,459 --> 00:09:53,739
Not like you can take it with you

253
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:55,180
when the contract ends anyway.

254
00:09:55,579 --> 00:09:56,700
No thanks.

255
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:00,300
I don't even have a driver's license.

256
00:10:02,220 --> 00:10:04,778
Why do you sound so proud
of not having a license?

257
00:10:04,779 --> 00:10:06,180
You're a grown adult.

258
00:10:06,220 --> 00:10:06,578
And you

259
00:10:06,579 --> 00:10:08,259
call yourself a PhD student?

260
00:10:31,699 --> 00:10:32,418
Mr. Huo,

261
00:10:32,419 --> 00:10:33,219
we're at the campus.

262
00:10:33,220 --> 00:10:34,739
Can we keep it low-key?

263
00:10:35,900 --> 00:10:36,899
Let's go.

264
00:10:37,140 --> 00:10:38,099
Where to now?

265
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:38,739
Shopping

266
00:10:38,740 --> 00:10:39,619
for a new outfit

267
00:10:39,620 --> 00:10:41,019
to get ready for the dinner party.

268
00:10:42,299 --> 00:10:43,060
Come on.

269
00:10:43,340 --> 00:10:44,739
Just buy whatever you want.

270
00:10:46,939 --> 00:10:48,619
Is there a budget limit?

271
00:10:48,620 --> 00:10:50,700
If I don't spend it all,
can I cash out the rest?

272
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:53,700
Not a chance.

273
00:10:53,860 --> 00:10:55,019
Get in. Come on.

274
00:10:55,020 --> 00:10:56,859
Cheapskate. Can we negotiate?

275
00:11:05,539 --> 00:11:07,180
The party starts at 7:00 p.m.

276
00:11:07,299 --> 00:11:08,739
It's rude to be late.

277
00:11:11,140 --> 00:11:12,660
What on earth is that noise?

278
00:11:14,339 --> 00:11:15,880
Are you doing makeup
or running lab tests?

279
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:17,058
If you stopped rushing me,

280
00:11:17,059 --> 00:11:19,379
my efficiency would shoot up
by at least 20%.

281
00:11:37,700 --> 00:11:41,299
♪Sometimes we roll the dice♪

282
00:11:41,300 --> 00:11:45,086
♪To see what the future hides♪

283
00:11:45,087 --> 00:11:51,270
♪Spinning us round and round
like a never-ending ride♪

284
00:11:51,887 --> 00:11:55,970
♪But I gave you everything♪

285
00:11:56,112 --> 00:11:59,620
♪Even the songs I loved to sing♪

286
00:12:15,137 --> 00:12:18,911
♪What destiny brought us to meet♪

287
00:12:18,912 --> 00:12:22,232
♪Two different worlds, a love so sweet♪

288
00:12:22,237 --> 00:12:25,611
♪A wish we made
in a past life, it seems♪

289
00:12:25,612 --> 00:12:28,466
♪Destined to cross time and dream ♪

290
00:12:28,467 --> 00:12:32,307
♪Like a fairytale story told♪

291
00:12:32,387 --> 00:12:35,644
♪A gentle breeze feels so bold♪

292
00:12:35,662 --> 00:12:39,348
♪As your hair brushes past your ear♪

293
00:12:39,349 --> 00:12:41,706
♪I long to kiss your cheek, my dear♪

294
00:12:41,707 --> 00:12:45,946
♪All my longing, all my love for you♪

295
00:12:45,947 --> 00:12:48,507
♪Has never changed, it's forever true♪

296
00:12:48,949 --> 00:12:55,347
♪It's the hand of fate
that we meet again♪

297
00:12:56,149 --> 00:13:00,587
♪Let me hold you once again♪

298
00:13:00,837 --> 00:13:03,757
♪Resting against your chest♪

299
00:13:04,107 --> 00:13:09,348
♪Your warmth shines like stars at night♪

300
00:13:09,349 --> 00:13:14,148
♪Let me kiss you once again♪

301
00:13:14,149 --> 00:13:16,948
♪No reason needed♪

302
00:13:16,949 --> 00:13:19,146
♪My heart belongs to you♪

303
00:13:19,147 --> 00:13:24,867
♪I'm not afraid
to cross time to find you♪

